"children":[
"Malaria"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s30_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Prevention"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c53b76",
"children":[
"Prevention"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"41b28c",
"children":[
"Select chloroquine for travelers to areas where chloroquine-resistant ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Plasmodium falciparum"
]
},
" has not been reported (Central America, Haiti, Dominican Republic). Otherwise, select mefloquine, atovaquone-proguanil, tafenoquine, or doxycycline."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s30_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis and Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"d7f1cf",
"children":[
"Diagnosis and Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"90261e",
"children":[
"Malaria is the most common cause of fever in returning travelers. Most infections are caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P. falciparum"
]
},
" or ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Plasmodium vivax"
]
},
", and most deaths are caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P. falciparum"
]
},
"."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e416ed",
"children":[
"Symptoms develop after an incubation period of 1 week to 3 months."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"330511",
"children":[
"Look for:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f6959b",
"children":[
"cyclical paroxysms of rigors"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"810eb6",
"children":[
"fever, drenching sweats"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"295c5d",
"children":[
"travel history and inadequate antimalarial prophylaxis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7519dd",
"children":[
"jaundice"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"23c6d1",
"children":[
"splenomegaly"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c3a952",
"children":[
"coma, seizure"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"380f43",
"children":[
"headache"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"506fe1",
"children":[
"Select thick and thin peripheral blood smears to diagnose malaria. Parasitemia levels >2% are most consistent with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P. falciparum"
]
},
" or ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Plasmodium knowlesi"
]
},
" (South and Southeast Asia) infection."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_id_f17"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8dc156",
"children":[
"Any traveler who has returned from a malaria-endemic area in the past year and has an undiagnosed febrile illness should undergo malaria evaluation."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s30_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9db73d",
"children":[
"For non-",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"falciparum"
]
},
" species or ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P. falciparum"
]
},
" acquired in chloroquine-sensitive areas, use chloroquine or hydroxychloroquine. For ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"P. falciparum"
]
},
" acquired in chloroquine-resistant areas, choose atovaquone-proguanil or artemether-lumefantrine."
]
}
]
}
]
},
